<abstract abstract-type="short" xml:lang="en"><p><![CDATA[Abstract Although climate change and global health are complex and intertwined phenomena, they still belong to different worlds. In order to identify interfaces between the two fields, this paper analyses the evolution of the International Regime on Climate Change: its features, obstacles, and key decisions.]]></p></abstract>
